---
/**
 * consensus-deep-dive · Figure 3 — the three FLP escape hatches
 * (randomisation / partial synchrony / full synchrony).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/distributed-systems/consensus-deep-dive.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). Isolated as an .astro component because MDX's JSX
 * parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes. It
 * references marker-end="url(#arw)" (fill #6b675f) AND marker-end="url(#arwG)"
 * (fill #2f5d3a); both arrowhead markers were declared once in the source's
 * top-of-body <svg defs> and are inlined here in a local <defs> so the figure
 * resolves standalone.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 158"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Three escape hatches from FLP: randomisation, partial synchrony, and synchrony, each restoring termination"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <rect
                x="14"
                y="40"
                width="120"
                height="56"
                rx="9"
                fill="#f7ecea"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="74"
                y="64"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">pure async</text
            >
            <text x="74" y="82" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f">FLP wall ✗</text
            >
            <line x1="134" y1="68" x2="184" y2="68" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <text x="159" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">relax one</text>
            <g>
                <rect x="186" y="14" width="200" height="34" rx="8" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="286"
                    y="30"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="10.5"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#2f5d3a">+ randomisation</text
                >
                <text x="286" y="43" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                    >Ben-Or — terminates w.p. 1</text
                >
                <rect x="186" y="54" width="200" height="34" rx="8" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="286"
                    y="70"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="10.5"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#2f5d3a">+ partial synchrony</text
                >
                <text x="286" y="83" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                    >Dwork–Lynch–Stockmeyer 1988</text
                >
                <rect x="186" y="94" width="200" height="34" rx="8" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="286"
                    y="110"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="10.5"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#2f5d3a">+ full synchrony</text
                >
                <text x="286" y="123" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                    >bounded delays → trivial</text
                >
            </g>
            <line x1="386" y1="68" x2="436" y2="68" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
            <rect x="438" y="40" width="150" height="56" rx="9" fill="#1c1b18"></rect>
            <text
                x="513"
                y="62"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#e8b3a6">safety ALWAYS</text
            >
            <text x="513" y="80" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#f3efe3"
                >liveness once calm</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Every real protocol below takes the <strong>partial-synchrony</strong> escape: keep safety always,
        get liveness once the network calms down.<sup><a href="#s2" id="r2">2</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
